6 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Historical Society;
amending 53 O.S. 2021, Sections 1.18, 171, and 201C,
7 as amended by Section 1, Chapter 213, O.S.L. 2022 (53
O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 201C), which relate to the
8 dispensation of funds; removing certain prohibition
on use of funds; updating statutory language;
9 updating statutory references; and providing an
effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 53 O.S. 2021, Section 1.18, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 1.18. The Oklahoma Historical Society shall dispense
16 funds for historical purposes only as defined provided by paragraph
17 6 of Section 6 of this act the Oklahoma Historical Preservation Act.
18 The Oklahoma Historical Society may enter into contracts with other
19 state agencies or nonprofit corporations holding a valid exemption
20 from taxation issued pursuant to Section 501(a) of the Internal
21 Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, and listed as an exempt
22 organization in Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code of
23 1986, of the United States, as amended, or with individuals or
24 associations pursuant to statutory requirements.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1307 Page 1

1 Funds shall not be applied, donated or used directly or
2 indirectly for the use, benefit or support of any sect, church,
3 denomination or system of religion, or for the use, benefit or
4 support of any priest, preacher, minister, or other religious
5 teacher or dignitary, or sectarian institution as such.
6 The Oklahoma Historical Society shall provide opportunity to
7 organizations to submit written applications to be received and
8 acted upon by the Oklahoma Historical Society. At the conclusion of
9 the contract, each state agency, nonprofit corporation, individual,
10 or association shall provide the Oklahoma Historical Society with
11 proof of fulfillment of the contract in proper order and must shall
12 be affirmed on the proper form, provided by the Oklahoma Historical
13 Society, by the managing officers of the state agency, nonprofit
14 group, association, or individual making the contract.
15 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 53 O.S. 2021, Section 171, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 171. The Oklahoma Arts Council shall dispense funds for
18 arts purposes only. The Oklahoma Arts Council shall enter into
19 contracts with other state agencies or nonprofit corporations
20 holding a valid exemption from taxation issued pursuant to Section
21 501(a) of the Internal Revenue Code, 1954 of 1986, as amended, and
22 listed as an exempt organization in Section 501(c)(3) of the
23 Internal Revenue Code, 1954, of the United States of 1986, as
24 amended. These nonprofit corporations must demonstrate that the
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1307 Page 2

1 good s and services provided meet the intent of the state policy
2 provided in this act Section 162 of this title.
3 Funds shall not be applied, donated or used directly or
4 indirectly for the use, benefit or support of any sect, church,
5 denomination or system of religion, or for the use, benefit, or
6 support of any priest, preacher, minister, or other religious
7 teacher or dignitary, or sectarian institution as such.
8 The Oklahoma Arts Council shall provide opportunity, by public
9 notices, to all organizations interested in providing these goods
10 and services, who will submit written applications to be received
11 and acted upon by the Oklahoma Arts Council. At the conclusion of
12 the contract, each state agency or nonprofit corporation shall
13 provide the Oklahoma Arts Council with proof of fulfillment of the
14 contract in proper order and must shall be affirmed on the proper
15 form, provided by the Oklahoma Arts Council, by the managing
16 officers of the state agency or nonprofit group making the contract.
17 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 53 O.S. 2021, Section 201C, as
18 amended by Section 1, Chapter 213, O.S.L. 2022 (53 O.S. Supp. 2025,
19 Section 201C), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 201C. A. The J.M. Davis Memorial Commission shall have
21 power and authority to:
22 1. Appoint and to fix the salaries and duties of the
23 professional and administrative employees and curators as may be
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1307 Page 3

1 nece ssary to carry out the purpose of this act 201A et seq. of this
2 title;
3 2. Appoint an executive director who shall serve at the
4 pleasure of the Commission. A member of the Commission may be
5 appointed as the executive director; provided, if a member of the
6 Commission is so appointed, the member shall resign as a member of
7 the Commission and the vacancy shall be filled in the same manner as
8 are original appointments;
9 3. Provide for the proper housing, protection and display of
10 the J.M. Davis Gun Collection and other historical artifacts; and
11 4. Enter into contracts for services to be performed in
12 furtherance of the authorized activities and duties of the J.M.
13 Davis Memorial Commission with other state agencies or nonprofit
14 corporations holding a valid exemption from taxation issued pursuant
15 to Section 501(a) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended,
16 and listed as an exempt organization in Section 501(c)(3) of the
17 Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, or with individuals or
18 associations pursuant to statutory requirements.
19 B. Funds of the J.M. Davis Memorial Commission shall not be
20 applied, donated, or used directly or indirectly for the use,
21 benefit, or support of any sect, church, denomination, or system of
22 religion, or for the use, benefit, or support of any priest,
23 preacher, minister, or other religious teacher or dignitary, or
24 sectarian institution as such. The J.M. Davis Memorial Commission
